@REMARK
@REMARK The Format-Nodes
@REMARK

@NODE "DMF"

The DMF Format

This format is used by the most powerful DTP program available
on any system. It's called PageStream 3.0 for Amiga (before you PC 
and Mac users start to complain, check it out first).

The files are a little smaller than the @{"Adobe" LINK "Adobe"} files, which can 
also be used within PageStream 3.0. It is faster though than the 
@{"Adobe" LINK "Adobe"} format.

Each directory contains the font file (.dmf), the metrics file (.fm) and
screen fonts (.??H) (?? = 12, 14, 18, 24).

@ENDNODE

@NODE "IntelliFont"

The Agfa-IntelliFont Format

This format is the standard Amiga fonts format which can be read by almost
any program on the Amiga. It is also widely spread on the Mac and not so
common on the PC.

The font consists only of one file (.type on the Amiga, .lib on the other
systems).

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Bitmap"

The Bitmap Format

These bitmap fonts can only be used on the Amiga (I don't have any
converters to other systems). The fonts normally have the following
sizes: 15, 30, 45, 60, 75, 100, 150.

The fonts can be either Black&White or Colour. The Colour Fonts have
various textures on them. Any Amiga Program can read them and the
colour fonts are especially useful for video production (e.g. Amiga 
Toaster System, Scala Multimedia etc.).

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Adobe"

The Adobe Format

The Adobe Format is used on any system a lot.

Each directory contains the following files:

#?.abf: Screen font
#?.afm: Font metrics
#?.pfb: Font in binary format (adobe type 1)
#?.pfa: Font in ascii format (adobe type 1)
#?.ps : Printer-Font (adobe type 3)
@ENDNODE

@REMARK
@REMARK The Sans Serif Drawer
@REMARK

@NODE "Sans Serif"

This drawer contains sans serif fonts.

  @{"Jupiter" LINK "Jupiter"}
  @{"Stuart" LINK "Stuart"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Jupiter"

Jupiter

This is a standard sans serif font. It can be used for standard
text. There are four types: medium, bold, italic and bolditalic.

Font Formats: - @{"Adobe" LINK "Adobe"} (Type 1 [pfa & pfb], Type 3, Bitmap)
              - @{"DMF" LINK "DMF"} (+ bitmap)
              - @{"Bitmap" LINK "Bitmap"} (Black&White)
              - @{"IntelliFont" LINK "IntelliFont"}

Font ID:      11000/11001/11002/11003

Directory:    Sans Serif/Jupiter

This font is freeware. Copyright © 1994 by @{"Danny Amor" LINK "Danny Amor"}.
You can copy this font with the readme files only!

This is how it looks like: 

  @{"Black&White medium" SYSTEM "SYS:Utilities/Multiview Pics/SansSerif/Jupiter.IFF"}
  @{"Black&White bold" SYSTEM "SYS:Utilities/Multiview Pics/SansSerif/Jupiter_bold.IFF"}
  @{"Black&White italic" SYSTEM "SYS:Utilities/Multiview Pics/SansSerif/Jupiter_italic.IFF"}
  @{"Black&White bolditalic" SYSTEM "SYS:Utilities/Multiview Pics/SansSerif/Jupiter_bolditalic.IFF"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Stuart"

Stuart

This is a broad sans serif font. It can be used for headings. There 
are four types: medium, bold, italic and bolditalic.

Font Formats: - @{"Adobe" LINK "Adobe"} (Type 1 [pfa & pfb], Type 3, Bitmap)
              - @{"DMF" LINK "DMF"} (+ bitmap)
              - @{"Bitmap" LINK "Bitmap"} (Black&White)
              - @{"IntelliFont" LINK "IntelliFont"}

Font ID:      11040/11041/11042/11043

Directory:    Sans Serif/Stuart

This font is freeware. Copyright © 1994 by @{"Danny Amor" LINK "Danny Amor"}.
You can copy this font with the readme files only!

This is how it looks like: 

  @{"Black&White medium" SYSTEM "SYS:Utilities/Multiview Pics/SansSerif/Stuart.IFF"}
  @{"Black&White bold" SYSTEM "SYS:Utilities/Multiview Pics/SansSerif/Stuart_bold.IFF"}
  @{"Black&White italic" SYSTEM "SYS:Utilities/Multiview Pics/SansSerif/Stuart_italic.IFF"}
  @{"Black&White bolditalic" SYSTEM "SYS:Utilities/Multiview Pics/SansSerif/Stuart_bolditalic.IFF"}

@ENDNODE

